{
  "texts": [
    "The study investigated six different gaits, including standing, level walking, going up the stairs, going down the stairs, going down the slope, and going down the slope.",
    "The authors demonstrated that the SVM outperformed Multilayer perceptron (MLP), and radial basis function (RBF) neural networks models.",
    "The study also analyzed the different sliding window sizes of the SVM algorithm.",
    "The results showed that the SVM algorithm had the highest recognition rate with an average recognition accuracy equal to 0.965%, tested on a total of 5H subjects.",
    "The accurate recognition of human gait provides a good theoretical basis for the design of a control strategy for a lower-limb exoskeleton."
  ]
}